SIMPLE: excellency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excellency
<hw>Ex"cel*len*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Excellencies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Excellence; virtue; dignity; worth; superiority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>excellency</qex> is over Israel.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. lxviii.
34.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Extinguish in men the sense of their own
<qex>excellency</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A title of honor given to certain high dignitaries,
esp. to viceroys, ministers, and ambassadors, to English colonial
governors, etc. It was formerly sometimes given to kings and
princes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excellent</ent>⟦br⟧
